	affiliations = {Higher Institute for Accounting and Financial Studies, University of Baghdad, Baghdad, Iraq; Department of Accounting, College of Administration and Economics, University of Baghdad, Baghdad, Iraq},
	abstract = {This study focuses on how tax administrations in Iraq use Artificial Intelligence (AI) techniques to monitor tax evasion for individuals and companies to achieve Tax Compliance (TC). AI was measured through four dimensions: Advanced Data Analytics Techniques (ADAT), Explainable AI (EAI), Machine learning (ML), and Robotic Process Automation (RPA). At the same time, TC was measured through registration, accounting, and tax payment stages. We relied on the questionnaire form to measure the variables. A sample of employees in the General Tax Authority in Iraq was selected, and a questionnaire was distributed to 132 people. The results indicated that the dimensions of AI affect achieving TC at all stages. This study provides evidence of using AI techniques to achieve TC in third-world countries. © The Author(s), under exclusive license to Springer Nature Switzerland AG 2025.},
